{% doc %}
  @prompt
    Market Position & Exclusivity
    
    As the exclusive distributor for GE PPE, WD-40 Microfiber Towels, and Best Value in the U.S. and Canada, Caco America secures defensible category positions in personal protective equipment, hardware, and consumer goods. These segments not only represent recession-resilient demand but also offer long-term scalability as safety standards, e-commerce penetration, and industrial consumption rise across North America.
    
    By holding exclusive rights, the company enjoys pricing power, brand control, and customer loyalty, while limiting competitive encroachment. This exclusivity builds a strategic moat and enables higher-margin operations compared to non-exclusive distribution models.
    
    Infrastructure & Operations
    
    The backbone of the business is its 10,000 m² warehouse facility, a high-capacity logistics center designed for speed, accuracy, and scalability. This facility underpins:
    
    Nationwide Shipping – Rapid fulfillment across the continental U.S. through optimized carrier partnerships and distribution networks.
    
    Cross-Border Capability – Infrastructure already in place to serve the Canadian market, enabling bi-national coverage.
    
    Multi-Channel Fulfillment – Simultaneous support for bulk B2B shipments and direct-to-consumer e-commerce orders, from pallets to parcels.
    
    Operating from Miami provides a strategic logistics advantage, with proximity to major seaports, airports, and intermodal connections. The location streamlines imports from Latin America, Europe, and Asia, reducing lead times and import costs, while offering a clear advantage over inland competitors.

{% enddoc %}
{% assign ai_gen_id = block.id | replace: '_', '' | downcase %}

{% style %}
